<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="346" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.9202/247:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Bandholtz</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                            Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-15">November 15, 1919</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                November 15—10:40 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>203. Polk from Bandholtz. Evacuation of Budapest by Roumanians and
                            reoccupation by Hungarians accomplished without noteworthy incident.
                            Shall return key to museum this date. Is report correct that Ammission
                            closes temporarily or permanently at end of November?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bandholtz</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>